<div id="ftn141"><p><a href="#_ftnref141" name="_ftn141" id="_ftn141"><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span>[141]</span></span></span></span></a>&#13;
An individuals rights with respect to access to his or her health&#13;
information are recognized in multiple statutory and regulatory instruments.&#13;
Freedom of Information Act, 5 U.S.C.A.  552 (West 2008); Privacy Act, 5&#13;
U.S.C.  552a (West 2008); Health Insurance Portability and Accountability&#13;
Act of 1996, Pub. L. No. 104-191, 110 Stat. 1936 (codified as amended in&#13;
scattered sections of 29 U.S.C. and 42 U.S.C.); ICE/DRO Detention Standard:&#13;
Medical Care, September 12, 2008, pp. 20-21; INS Detention Standard,&#13;
Medical Care, September 20, 2000, p. 9.</p></div>
